Some members of the All Progressives Congress (APC) in Kwara State have defected to the opposition Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) in the state. Those who defected were from  Kwara North Senatorial District, stronghold of Governor AbdulRahman AbdulRazaq. The former APC members officially announced their decision to join the PDP at a brief ceremony held at the state secretariat of the PDP in Ilorin. Due to social distancing protocol of COVID-19, only representatives of the the decampees picked from across the five local government areas of Kwara North Senatorial District  were at the PDP secretariat. The leader of the group,  Manzuma Kawu Dogo claimed that “We are over 10,000 in number across the 58 wards in the district “. Dear valued readers, subscribe to the Daily Trust e-paper to continue enjoying our diet of authoritative news. Kindly subscribe here Welcoming the decampees, the PDP state chairman, Engr Kola Shittu, described the development as unprecedented, assuring the new members that they would enjoy same rights the existing party members  enjoy. Saraki receives 3000 APC defectors in Kwara APC Kicks as traditional rulers bless PDP Kwara guber pact Badaru, Ringim, Adamu battle for the soul of Jigawa